ids":["n27409","n27417"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"good, wholesome, nice, fine (for example, beneficial, favorable, advantageous; moral, pure, clean; nutritious, nourishing, healthy; tasty, delicious, pleasant, etc.)","examples":[{"text":"كُلُوا مِن طَيِّبَاتِ مَا رَزَقْنَاكُمْ وَلا تَطْغَوْا فِيهِ فَيَحِلَّ عَلَيْكُمْ غَضَبِي وَمَن يَحْلِلْ عَلَيْهِ غَضَبِي فَقَدْ هَوَى","english":"ُO Children of Israel! Eat from the good and wholesome things of what We have allotted to you, and do not transgress with it, so My wrath does not come down upon you. Whomever My wrath comes down upon has lapsed."},{"text":"فمضينا ومعنا من الغناء والآلة والشراب كل شيء ظريف، وأقمنا بالعمر ثلاثة أيام، ومضت لنا به أوقات طيبة،"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"charming, pleasant, agreeable"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"enjoyable"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"tasty, palatable"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَابَ (ṭāba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goodness, kind-heartedness; agreeability"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fragrance, scent, perfume","examples":[{"text":"لَا طِيبَ يَعْدِلُ تُرْبًا ضَمَّ أَعْظُمَهُ","english":"No perfume equals the dust (earth) which is touching his body."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to season, to spice (food)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make pleasant, to make sweet"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perfume, to aromatise"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṭāb- (“good, pleasant”), with levelling to the typical Arabic adjective pattern CayyiC of hollow roots. Cognate with Akkadian 𒁕𒁍𒌝 (ṭābum) and Biblical Hebrew טוֹב (ṭoḇ).\n\nCompare Sabaean 𐩷𐩺𐩨 (ṭyb, “lemongrass”) and Akkadian 𒁵 (ṭabtum, “goodness; salt”)."},"ipa":["/tˤaj.jib/","/tˤiːb/","/tˤaj.ja.ba/"]}